This method consists of two steps: First, we generated a random covariance (connectivity) matrix using the Python scikit library [71]. In order to apply the Cholesky method to construct a ROI activity matrix from the connectivity matrix, the starting connectivity matrix must be symmetric positive-definite in linear algebra [53]. Second, we created a ROI activity matrix that matched the above connectivity matrix, using the Cholesky method (53). The connectivity matrix CCell × Cell was decomposed into two parts: L and LT. We then generated a random matrix (cell x time). For any given random matrix XCell × Time, the simulated ROI activity time series matrix SCell × Time was as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
